Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (markedly elevated creatinine), proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, high protein, glucose, and ketones). Blood glucose and HbA1c are low, suggesting hypoglycemia rather than diabetes. No evidence of urinary infection. Findings are consistent with acute or chronic kidney dysfunction, possibly nephrotic syndrome or acute glomerulonephritis. Immediate nephrology evaluation is recommended.
